                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="13977039" author="junrao" created="Tue, 22 Apr 2014 16:49:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue seems to be there is no resend in the test. We should configure enough retries (default to 0) and retry backoff time to allow metadata to be propagated to the broker after auto topic creation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13977083" author="guozhang" created="Tue, 22 Apr 2014 17:26:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this is a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1395&quot; title=&quot;fix unit tests in AutoOffsetResetTest&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-1395&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-1395&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. My proposal is to unify createProducer to ensure acks = -1 and type = sync, in which after the send call if no exception is thrown for failed message sending we are assured that the topic is created, hence no need to check waitUntilMetadataIsPropagated either.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13986760" author="junrao" created="Thu, 1 May 2014 16:52:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created reviewboard  against branch origin/trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13986763" author="junrao" created="Thu, 1 May 2014 16:53:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created reviewboard &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/20954/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/20954/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 against branch origin/trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13987178" author="junrao" created="Thu, 1 May 2014 23:36:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the reviews. Committed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
